{"id": "1419904902624182413", "channel_id": "1419179851272814602", "type": 0, "author_id": "1400733999000977510", "author_name": "wisteriavine11", "author_bot": false, "content": "So far the KR team has prioritized on retranslating names first, and we're planning to work on skill mechanics and gameplay next. (meaning, we haven't worked on the Arg texts that much yet)\nMost of our translations are based on CN text because 漢字", "timestamp": "2025-09-23T04:35:09.343000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "celeste_pray", "emoji_id": "1408324281624170566", "count": 1}], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1419179851272814602", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "如何解決翻譯與校對人員的同步編輯衝突問題？", "forum_channel_id": "1404748432328888401", "thread_tags": ["1404748529724952576", "1410391772894330961", "1404748570871201913"]}
{"id": "1419928821938913311", "channel_id": "1419179851272814602", "type": 0, "author_id": "147364225411579904", "author_name": "strandiel", "author_bot": false, "content": "I can chime in on the DE team, we don't have anyone who knows CN even the slightest bit and we're only two people.\n\nWe're trying to do EN -> DE, and double check by either asking in here about the meaning of CN, or hope that deepl or any other online translator gives an accurate result, which usually won't be the case. \n\nThat, for example, came up when I was proofreading Hameln's texts, and then had to reproofread them after Cassius made them make way more sense by fixing the EN.\n\nWe can wait until someone from EN finishes translating something properly and then fix the German based on the correct English.", "timestamp": "2025-09-23T06:10:12.152000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": "2025-09-23T06:14:02.261000+00:00", "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1419179851272814602", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "如何解決翻譯與校對人員的同步編輯衝突問題？", "forum_channel_id": "1404748432328888401", "thread_tags": ["1404748529724952576", "1410391772894330961", "1404748570871201913"]}
